election_record.label: Vermont 1816 U.S. House of Representatives

overview.note: The Official Election Results aggregate tally sheet lists Mark Richards with 16836 votes, William Hunter with 16794 votes, Samuel C. Crafts with 16582 votes, Charles Rich with 16596 votes, Orsamus C. Merrill with 16611 votes, Heman Allen with 16614 votes, Asa Lyon with 13846 votes, Chauncey Langdon with 13926 votes, David Edmond with 13842 votes, Jonathan C. Hubbard with 13876 votes, Phineas White with 13866 votes and Samuel Prentiss with 13728 votes.

sub_unit.name: Addison
sub_unit.note: The Official Election Results tally sheet lists Samuel C. Crafts with 1300 votes, Charles Rich with 1420 votes and Herman Allen with 1435 votes.

sub_unit.name: Bridport
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet does not list any votes for Samuel C. Crafts in Bridport.

sub_unit.name: Bennington
sub_unit.note: The Official Election Results tally sheet lists Heman Allen with 1229 votes.

sub_unit.name: Wheelock
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet does not list any votes for Samuel C. Crafts or Charles Rich in Wheelock.

sub_unit.name: Chittenden
sub_unit.note: The Official Election Results tally sheet lists Heman Allen with 944 votes, Asa Lyon with 979 votes, Chauncey Langdon with 1135 votes, David Edmonds with 1132 votes, Jonathan C. Hubbard with 1134 votes, Phineas White with 1133 votes and Samuel Prentiss with 1134 votes.

sub_unit.name: Essex
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet does not list any votes for Samuel Prentiss in Essex.

sub_unit.name: Jericho
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet does not list any votes for Asa Lyon in Jericho.

sub_unit.name: Westford
sub_unit.note: The votes from Westford were rejected and are not listed on the Original Election Returns tally sheet. These figures come from the Westford Town Records.

sub_unit.name: Granby
sub_unit.note: There were no votes recorded in Granby.

sub_unit.name: Franklin
sub_unit.note: The Official Election Results tally sheet lists Mark Richards with 1001 votes and Samuel Prentiss with 1063 votes.

sub_unit.name: Orange
sub_unit.note: The Official Election Results tally sheet lists Charles Rich with 1992 votes.

sub_unit.name: Fairlee
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet does not list any votes for Charles Rich in Fairlee.

sub_unit.name: Orleans
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet lists 447 votes for Heman Allen, 475 votes for Asa Lyon, 475 votes for David Edmond, 475 votes for Jonathan Hubbard, 474 votes for Phineas White and 475 votes for Samuel Prentiss; however, the sum of totals per town is 446 for Allen, 473 votes for Lyon, 449 votes for Edmond, 473 votes for Hubbard, 472 votes for White and 473 votes for Prentiss.

sub_unit.name: Glover
sub_unit.note: Twenty-four votes for Daniel Edmonds in Glover have been added to the total for David Edmond.

sub_unit.name: Kellyvale
sub_unit.note: Kellyvale Town Records reports no votes for the Republican ticket.

sub_unit.name: Washington
sub_unit.note: The Official Election Results tally sheet lists Orasmus C. Merrill with 894 votes.

sub_unit.name: Marshfield
sub_unit.note: The votes from Marshfield are not recorded on the Original Election Returns. These figures come from the Marshfield Town Records.

sub_unit.name: Plainfield
sub_unit.note: The Original Election Returns tally sheet does not list any votes for Orasmus C. Merrill in Plainfield.

sub_unit.name: Windham
sub_unit.note: The Official Election Results tally sheet lists Charles Rich with 1495 votes and Heman Allen with 1481 votes.

sub_unit.name: Windsor
sub_unit.note: The Official Election Results tally sheet lists William Hunter with 3240 votes, Samuel C.
